</div><div class="author"></div>
    <p>"Fiat" is not an acronym, so when you capitalize it you look ignorant. Like people who say I can't find the right mouse button on my MAC.</p>
<p>"Fiat" a latin word which means "let it be". And this is literally where the definition of fiat money comes from. Fiat is money which derives its value from a *legal decree*.</p>
<p>The thing that sets bitcoin apart from fiat money is... that it's not, by definition, fiat money. Bitcoin is commodity money, like gold or silver. There is no authority who declares it to be money or regulates its value. It is traded in the marketplace and its value is agreed to only through voluntary trade.</p>

